To create a PostgreSQL database user named kodekloud_tim with the password dCV3szSGNA, follow these steps:
Connect to PostgreSQL: Access the PostgreSQL command-line interface (psql) as a superuser (e.g., postgres).
Code

    sudo -i -u postgres psql
Create the user: Execute the CREATE USER command within the psql prompt.
Code

    CREATE USER kodekloud_tim WITH PASSWORD 'dCV3szSGNA';
Exit psql.
Code

    \q

To create a PostgreSQL database named kodekloud_db4 and grant full permissions to the user kodekloud_tim on this database, perform the following steps:
Connect to PostgreSQL as a superuser (e.g., postgres user):
Code

    sudo -u postgres psql
Create the user kodekloud_tim (if they don't already exist):
Replace your_password_here with a strong password.
Code

    CREATE USER kodekloud_tim WITH ENCRYPTED PASSWORD 'your_password_here';
Create the database kodekloud_db4.
Code

    CREATE DATABASE kodekloud_db4;
Grant all privileges on the database kodekloud_db4 to the user kodekloud_tim: 
Code

    GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE kodekloud_db4 TO kodekloud_tim;
Exit the PostgreSQL prompt.
Code

    \q
